# Comms Module

## Scope
Public-facing guides and image generation tools. v1 shipped as static export.

## Public nav
Learn menu must keep **By channel** (Print, Union Boards, Website guides) — see `.cursor/rules/comms-public-nav.mdc` and `docs/modules/COMMS.md`. Backlog ideas (email guide, consent checklist, Get started beyond social): `docs/modules/COMMS_BACKLOG.md`. Calendar/meeting scope: `docs/modules/CALENDAR_MEETINGS.md`, `.cursor/rules/calendar-meetings.mdc`.

## Meeting announcement tools (not scheduling or reminders)

Board Notice (`noticeType: "meeting"`), Document Generator `quick-event`, Graphic Maker `meetingNotice`, and Meeting Backgrounds help locals **communicate about** meetings via PNG/PDF/doc export. They do not store events, send email, or push reminders. Officers re-enter details each month.

## Rules
- All image/document processing client-side (html-to-image, JSZip, jsPDF, docx, ExcelJS, pptxgenjs)
- PNG capture (`exportNodeAsPng`): keep `shadow-*` outside `canvasRef`; pass explicit hex `backgroundColor`; inside the capture node use inline hex/`rgba` only — no Tailwind `text-white*`, `opacity-*`, or `bg-white` (oklch washout). See solidarity-poster / `graphic-layouts.tsx`.
- **Auto contrasting ink** (required on export canvases): use `pickContrastingInk(background)` from `@/lib/utils/ink` for titles, body, and footer copy. Prefer `BrandLogo` + `backgroundColor={canvasHex}` over hardcoding `onDark` / `#FFFFFF` — ink auto-swaps to black on pale primaries and white on dark/brand fields. Use `inkWithAlpha(ink, a)` for muted copy. Never force white text/logos on a light primary.
- **Logo monochrome**: when ink is forced, `BrandLogo` uses official white mark assets or CSS `filter` (`logoRasterFilter`) for lockups/custom uploads. Prefer filter over `mask-image` — masks do not survive html-to-image capture.
- Office exports via `src/lib/export/office-export.ts` + `OfficeExportButton` — Document Generator builds Word with the `docx` library from Brand Kit colours/logo; ExcelJS RSVP sheets; pptxgenjs decks; ZIP bundles. Route: `/tools/document-generator`
- Member photo uploads require `ConsentModal` confirmation
- Colour pickers must show `ContrastChecker` warnings
- Tool pages use `useUndoRedo` for edit history
- Display/export local number via `resolveLocalNumber()` from `@/lib/utils/local`
- Brand state via `useBrandStore` / `DataAdapter`
- Logo: `BrandLogo` for display; `LogoSettings` for official/custom upload (PNG/JPEG/WebP/SVG)
- Platform UnionOps mark: interlocking u+o inline SVG in `UnionOpsMark` — primary plate + accent glyph; light ink → white plate; dark ink → black plate + white glyph (inline SVG so PNG export works)
- See `.cursor/rules/opseu-branding.mdc` for OPSEU/CAAT colour rationale
- Solidarity board posters: `.cursor/rules/solidarity-posters.mdc` (`/tools/solidarity-poster`)
- Meeting backgrounds (Zoom/Teams): `.cursor/rules/meeting-backgrounds.mdc` (`/tools/meeting-background`) — solidarity energy, face-safe layouts
- QR link cards: `/tools/qr-card` (client `qrDataUrl`, multi-size print)
- QR board posters: `/tools/qr-board` (multi-QR letter/tabloid board sheets)

## Multi-Union Migration (Phase 1)
Replace hardcoded OPSEU/CAAT strings with tenant `UnionConfig`.
See `docs/modules/COMMS.md` for migration checklist.

## Do Not
- Send user data to servers in v1
- Skip consent flow for member spotlight graphics
- Hardcode union-specific branding in new components
- Hardcode `#FFFFFF` / `onDark` on brand-coloured export canvases when the canvas hex is known — use `pickContrastingInk` / `backgroundColor`
- Use CSS `mask-image` inside PNG capture nodes for logo tinting
